The paper deals with the design of beamforming for a wireless communication system, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The optimization problem formulation and solution techniques involve control and optimization (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MM) concepts. The simulation results and performance analysis can also be related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
